node.text:
Gustav Ludwig Hertz, the nephew of the Heinrich Rudolf Hertz, is known worldwide for his famous work on inelastic collisions in the gases for which he did receive the Nobel Prize in 1925 with James Franck. He also served in the military during World War I, where chlorine gas was introduced as a weapon but the entire situation wounded him seriously after which he returned to  Berlin as the Privatdozent at the Philips Incandescent Lamp Factory in Eindhoven as a research fellow.In 1928, he  became the director of the Physics Institute at Charlottenburg Technological University in Berlin. Hertz also devised an unique technique called the diffused cascade to separate the isotopes of helium and neon, which was crucial for the uses of nuclear energy and uranium isotopes. He was also actively involved in Union Soviet, where he dedicated himself to the nuclear research and development of radioactive isotopes. Indeed Gustav Hertz had been a great experimental physicist of all the times.
 On the auspicious day of 22nd July, ISTE NIT Durgapur celebrates his birthday paying  numinous empyrean benevolence and altruism to him.

#science #nobelprizewinner #innovations #istenitdgp

node.text:
It all started four years ago, as you embarked on this journey at a new place with new people. As days passed, they became unforgettable. With a glint of positivity and happiness, let us cherish all that has happened, we will always be indebted to you for all the countless life lessons you have given us.
Dear seniors, your wisdom, work, and achievements will be remembered forever. You were instrumental in the grand success of our year-long activities and a plethora of events round the year. You will be dearly missed amongst us, We just hope you know how proud we are to be associated with you; to be called your juniors. We still are at a loss of words to express our gratitude to you. We understand Goodbye often comes in waves and you have much more to offer to the society and community at large. Every new beginning comes from some other beginning's end. This is the beginning of anything you want.
May you achieve all your dreams, overcome all challenges, and sail successfully in the wonderful voyage of life. 
You all will be missed but never forgotten!!

Quarantine may have kept us wishing for more, but these creative products and their innovative marketing surely had us wishing for them!

Congratulations to the winners of UP THE ANTE!

Winner: The team of Yashrajsinh Solanki, Maharsh Shah, Rudram Vyas, Aditya Mistry (Nirma University) for their Anywhere Door!

Judging criteria: Innovation, Creativity, Marketing

#marketing #creativity #results #spectrum #iste

It was an intense four rounds of coding, with the showcase of ingenious skill. But alas, there can only be one victor.

Congratulations to the winners of DREAM CODEX!

Winner: Mangroliya Vishvas Dilipbhai (Nirma University)

First Runner up: Nikhil Nair  (Nirma University)

Second Runner up: Vasu Mavani  (Nirma University)

Note, the winners have been selected based on their performance in all four rounds.

The king was on the chessboard, but our participants showed true royalty in playing the matches.

Congratulations to the winners of MONARCH VICTORY!

Winner: Anmol Agarwal (Symbiosis Centre for Management Studies)

First Runner up: Soumyadip Deb (NIT Durgapur)

Second Runner up: Showmith Chowdhury (Barasat MGM High School)

The world wouldn’t be the same if it weren’t for the contributions of scientists and technologists. The  submitted entries were a fitting tribute to these impactful personalities.

Congratulations to the winners of RETROSPECTIVE!

Winner: Pratiksha Patel (NIT Durgapur)

First Runner up: Arnab Ari (NIT Durgapur)

The winner's entries have been attached in the order mentioned.

Judging criteria: Creativity, Originality, Clarity

Doctors can be rightly called as saviours since they are the ones who not only cure and heal us but also save us from the clutches of death lending us the chance to lead a happy and joyful life all over again. They are the ones who serve the society selflessly all round the clock and devote their lives for the well being of mankind. Doctor's Day is celebrated on the 1st of July every year in India to mark the birth and death anniversary of Dr. Bidhan Chandra Roy,the second Chief Minister of West Bengal and one of the greatest doctors of all times . In the current pandemic scenario,doctors as well as every health workers are fighting against Covid-19 selflessly at the cost of their lives only to cure us from this disease. Thus , it's our moral duty not only to salute and be grateful to  them and thier works but also to support them in every possible way appreciating their works  since they are relentlessly engaged in their jobs.
 ISTE NIT Durgapur salutes and pays homage to all the doctors and the heath workers all across the country since they are true heroes ready to serve the society at all times and urges everyone to support and stand by them whole heartedly at all times.

#doctors #oursavior #healthworkers

First Runner up: Dayeeta Pal (NIT Durgapur) & Devansshi Jhaveri (Nirma University)

Compelling stories and intriguing conspiracies kept us glued to our seats. Our grey cells were definitely piqued, and choosing the best was no easy task.

Congratulations to the winners of SLEUTH’S VISION!

Winner: Praneetha Dinesh (NIT Calicut) for her very compelling God conspiracy

First Runner up: Love Kush Pranu (NIT Calicut) for his innovative take on the origins of the Coronavirus

Second Runner up: Swathy Suresh B. (NIT Calicut) for her insightful theory on the Indo-Pak partition & Chaitashi Pandya (Nirma University) for her interesting conspiracy on Hitler's death

The winner’s entries can be read on the blog link in our bio.
Judging criteria: Writing skills, Creativity, Intrigue of the topic chosen

#results #spectrum #iste

Drive away your quarantine blues with one of the most ancient games- chess! But this is no ordinary game, for in blitz chess, time is your friend and your foe. Beginner or expert, there’s a place for everyone in MONARCH VICTORY.

Race against the clock, beat your opponents, and play as many matches to gain points. To participate, click on the Lichess link in our bio (which will be made available at 5:45 pm). For more details about the tournament, refer to https://lichess.org/tournament/help?system=arena

NOTE: The app is preferred over the website. Organizers will not be responsible for any network issue. But if technical problems arise (i.e. with the server), then the duration of the tournament will be increased. The use of chess engines is strictly prohibited; any player reported doing so will be immediately disqualified.

#chess #monarchvictory #spectrum #iste #staytuned
